cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DL 

The paper focuses on the relationship between scientific impact and online demand and supply for information about scientists and their work. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as well as digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of temporal patterns of information supply and demand also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.SD). Finally, the study compares two groups of scientists based on their awards, which could be considered a form of classification (cs.CY).
